description: {"blocks":[{"key":"2mesc","text":"Receptor-ligand binding has been analyzed at the protein level using isothermal titration calorimetry and surface plasmon resonance and at the cellular level using interaction-associated downstream gene induction/suppression. However, no currently available technique can characterize this interaction directly through visualization. In addition, all available assays require a large pool of cells; no assay capable of analyzing receptor-ligand interactions at the single-cell level is publicly available. Here, we describe a new microfluidic chip–based technique for analyzing and visualizing these interactions at the single-cell level. First, a protein is immobilized on a glass slide and a low-flow-rate pump is used to isolate cells that express receptors that bind to the immobilized ligand. Specifically, we demonstrate the efficacy of this technique by immobilizing biotin-conjugated FGL2 on an avidin-coated slide chip and passing a mixture of GFP-labeled wild-type T cells and RFP-labeled FcγRIIB-knockout T cells through the chip. Using automated scanning and counting, we found a large number of GFP+ T cells with binding activity but significantly fewer RFP+ FcγRIIB-knockout T cells. We further isolated T cells expressing a membrane-anchored, tumor-targeted IL-12 based on the receptor’s affinity to vimentin to confirm the versatility of our technique. This protocol allows researchers to isolate receptor-expressing cells in about 4 hours for further downstream processing.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"apcu4","text":"Extract and homogenize the spleens of FcγRIIB-KO (Taconic, model no. 580) and C57/BL6 mice (Jackson Labs, cat. no. 000664) with a 40-μm mesh filter.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b4oec","text":"Isolate T Cells from the homogenized cells by using a MojoSort Mouse CD3 T cell Isolation Kit (BioLegend, cat. no. 480023).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3nojl","text":"Label T cells from WT mice with CellTracker Green BODIPY dye (Thermo Fisher Scientific, cat. no. C2102), and T cells from FcγRIIB-KO mice with CellTracker Red CMTPX dye (Thermo Fisher Scientific, cat. no. C34552).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"80opd","text":"Immobilize FGL2 on the microfluidic chip by covering a polydimethylsiloxane-coated microfluidic chip with 1 mg/mL streptavidin (Sigma, cat. no. 189730) for 1 hour at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1t093","text":"Coat the chip with 32 μg of biotin-conjugated FGL2 suspended in 100 μL of phosphate-buffered saline (PBS) for 1 hour at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fqvi5","text":"Mix 5 × 106 FcγRIIB-KO T cells (red) and 1.5 × 106 WT T cells (green) and resuspend in 100 μL of T Cell media. 2.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":10,"length":1},{"style":"sup","offset":49,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4jp8s","text":"Connect a spiral chamber containing microfluidic tubing to the Abnova CytoQuest microfluidic pump.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"48br2","text":"Prime for capture of WT T cells by washing with PBS and water.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"dmag2","text":"Attach the chamber to the pump and allow flow process to initiate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2323p","text":"Temporarily disconnect the chamber from the pump and place the end tubing into an Eppendorf tube containing the T-cell mixture. The pump will draw the T cells into the chamber tubing and then passed the cell mixture through the slide chip. Only cells that display strong binding to the recombinant FGL2 protein will remain on the microfluidic chip. Cells that do not bind strongly will pass through the microfluidic chip into a waste container.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5j9o8","text":"Image the microfluidic chip with an automated Keyence microscope (www.keyence.com, model no. BZX-710) at 20× magnification.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3t8sk","text":"Assign individual set points and image for fluorescein isothiocyanate and phycoerythrin channels.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1lck4","text":"Use the BZX-800 analysis software (Keyence) to count the cells on the resulting images. Count individual images were ‘stitch mode’ in groups of 400 until every image is counted.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
